[{"id":"FT584553","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p><img alt=\"The figure shows a graph with a horizontal axis labeled Number of Workers, and a vertical axis labeled Wage Rate in dollars. Three quantities appear on the horizontal axis and are labeled, from left to right, 15, 40, and 90. One wage rate is listed on the vertical axis and is labeled 10.  The graph contains one straight and one curved line. The straight line is parallel to the horizontal axis, starts on the vertical axis at the $10 point, and is labeled Market Wage. The curved line starts above the horizontal axis, to the right of the vertical axis, and is labeled M R P. The M R P slopes sharply upward and to the right, passes through the Market Wage line at the coordinates 15 workers and $10 wage rate, continues upward and to the right, reaches its peaks at the coordinate for 40 workers, then it gently slopes downward to the right, passes through the Market Wage line at the coordinate for 90 workers, and ends before reaching the horizontal axis.\" height=\"238\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/866498ca129aa61dec4e04220c6ed811/original.png\" width=\"285\" /></p>\n\n<p>The graph above shows the marginal revenue product (MRP) and the market wage rate for</p>\n\n<p>a profit-maximizing firm. Which of the following is true of the firmâ€™s hiring of labor?</p>\n","choicesHtml":["<p>It should hire 15 workers.</p>","<p>It should hire between 15 and 40 workers.</p>","<p>It should hire 40 workers.</p>","<p>It should hire between 40 and 90 workers.</p>","<p>It should hire 90 workers.</p>"],"answer":3}]